title: Australian market set to open higher
text:
Thursday closed nearly 1.5 per cent higher.
 slightly higher after US and European bourses closed lower on global growth fears and amid the spreading Volkswagen scandal. At 0645 AEST on Friday, the six points at 5,064.
No major economic is expected on Friday.
In equities news, Australia Post is expected to release its full year results.
Meanwhile, Oz Minerals chief executive Andrew Cole is slated to speak at an AICC lunch in Adelaide.
